Center: Centre for Photonuclear Experiments Data, Moscow State University, Russia
ref: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.35, p.1828 (1987)
title: The (G,P), (G,Pn), and (G,Pp) Reactions On Light Nuclei In The Delta (1232) Resonance Region.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.35, p.1828 (1987)

x4freetext: NUCLEI IN THE DELTA (1232) RESONANCE REGION.
UNIVERSITY OF TOKIO 1.3 GEV ELECTRON SYNCHROTRON.
THE NUCLEAR TARGETS WERE 1H (HYDROGEN IN WATER,
CONTAINER OF THE DISTILLED WATER MADE OF MYLAR
FILMS 127 MICRON THICK, 200 MM IN DIAMETER, AND
CONTAINER MADE OF MYLAR FILM 127 MICRON THICK,
60 MM IN DIAMETER, AND 123 MM LONG), 9BE (NATURAL
BERILLIUM PLATE WITH SIZES OF 50 X 50 X 10 MM**3),
100 X 150 X 11 MM**3), AND 16O (OXYGEN IN WATER).
THE CROSS SECTIONS OF THE REACTIONS (G,P), (G,PN),
16O IN THE DELTA (1232) RESONANCE REGION BY USE OF
TAGGED PHOTON BEAM. PROTONS EMITTED AT THETA-P =
30 DEGREE WERE MEASURED BY A MAGNETIC SPECTROMETER,
AND THE OTHER NEUTRONS OR PROTONS WERE MEASURED
BY AN ARRAY OF SCINTILLATION COUNTER HODOSCOPES.
FROM THE PRESENT EXPERIMENT, IT WAS CONCLUDED THAT
THE REACTIONS, G + "N" -> P + PI AND G + "PN" -> P
+ N, CONTRIBUTE DOMINANTLY TO THE (G,P) REACTION
IN THIS ENERGY REGION, WHERE "N" DENOTES THE
NUCLEON AND "PN" DENOTES THE PN SYSTEMS IN THE
DATA WERE COMPILED AT THE USA BNL NNDC BY
